  <!-- Síntesis de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="synthesis-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Invite two students to come to the front of the room with their cube towers.</li>
      <li>
        <q>¿Cómo podemos usar 'más, 'menos' y 'el mismo número' para hablar de estas torres?</q>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Descripción del desarrollo de lenguaje matemático -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="language-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>MLR8 Discussion Supports. To provide all students with opportunities to practice, invite students to chorally repeat phrases that include “more,” “fewer,” and “the same number,” in unison multiple times.</p>
    <p>Advances: Listening, Speaking]</p>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Estrategias de acceso para estudiantes con discapacidades -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="accesibility-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Action and Expression: Internalize Executive Functions. Check for understanding by inviting 1–2 students to rephrase directions in their own words.</p>
    <p>Supports accessibility for: Memory, Organization</p>
  </paragraphs>

</postlude>

